process.name: OnDemand Document Extract
process.narrative: Retrieves all of the documents for a given Claim Number and OnDemand folder and saves them to PDF

condition.narrative: Provided with OnDemand User ID and Password, Server Name (currently only works for Prod), the root document folder path, the path to the excel spreadsheet containing the queries, and the OnDemand folder name to be searched

endpoint.narrative: Folders are created for each Claim Number to be queried for the specified OnDemand Folder, and the document images are saved in each associated Claim Number folder as well as an excel spreadsheet list of document data

input.name: Excel Document File Path
input.narrative: Column A with header "Claim Number' and Column B with header 'Search Criteria'

stage.name: Note1
stage.narrative: This loop handles all of the documents which are stored as OnDemand images, not PDFs, by only printing to PDF if the "Correspondence Name" field is not blank

stage.name: Note2
stage.narrative: This loop handles all of the documents which are already stored as PDFs, by opening the PDF in Acrobat and printing it as PDF again

stage.name: Note1
stage.narrative: This error check is necessary in case OnDemand's load times are slow. If the document list has not yet loaded then it will wait 10 seconds (some of the load times are this long) and then try again

stage.name: Note4
stage.narrative: These are the Start Up Parameters, to be filled out accordingly based on which folder you are searching

stage.name: Note5
stage.narrative: View Bill Image and View EBS Data are formatted differently because of the large amount of document numbers that need to be individually queried, thus the file exist check occurs within the loop itself

stage.name: Note6
stage.narrative: For any folder not searching with document number, if the folder already exists within your directory, it will not perform the document extract for that claim number

stage.name: Note8
stage.narrative: Each Folder has different fields, thus each excel document must be formatted differently depending on the folder being searched

input.name: File Name
input.narrative: The name of the file to check

stage.name: Go To Next Empty Cell
stage.narrative: This is the cell where the data is pasted

input.name: handle
input.narrative: The integer handle identifying the instance on which the required cell should be sought. The default of zero indicates the currently active instance.

input.name: Direction
input.narrative: The direction in which the next empty cell is required. This should start with any of "U", "D", "L" or "R" to find a cell up, down, left or right respectively. The direction parameter is not case-sensitive.

input.name: Activate Cell?
input.narrative: True to activate the cell which is found; False to just return the reference and leave the active cell as it was before. Default is False.

output.name: Cell Reference
output.narrative: The cell reference identifying the next empty cell from the active cell in the direction given. An empty value indicates that there were no empty cells between the active cell and a boundary.

input.name: Cell Reference
input.narrative: The cell reference on the currently active sheet within the specified instance which should be navigated to.

input.name: handle
input.narrative: The integer handle identifying the instance on which the required workbook should be opened. The default of zero indicates the currently active instance.

input.name: File name
input.narrative: The path and name of the file which should be opened.

output.name: Workbook Name
output.narrative: The name used by Excel to identify the workbook - usually this is the file name (without the path).
